ORBIS Case Link: [OC-1752|https://orbiscompliance.my.salesforce.com/a24RQ000002ChODYA0]

*Description:* 
Implement an endpoint that allows retrieving *complete project details* from Salesforce, including related account, contact, localholder, and associated model information. The API must integrate with the existing _bridge_ .

*Endpoint:* 
GET /projects /:project _id

*Response (structural example):*

{noformat}{

  "project_id": "",

  "project_name": "",

  "status": "",

  "Account": {

    "account_id": "",

    "account_name": "",

    "url_logo": ""

  },

  "Contact": {

    "contact_id": "",

    "name": "",

    "email": ""

  },

  "Localholder": {

    "id": "",

    "name": ""

  },

  "Models": [

    {

      "model_sf_id": "",

      "brand": "",

      "model": "",

      "product_name": "",

      "commercial_name": ""

    }

  ]

}{noformat}

 

*Acceptance criteria (AC):*

* Develop the *GET API* to obtain project details from Salesforce.
* Integrate the API with the corresponding *bridge*.
* *Document* the endpoint in *Confluence* (definition, parameters, and response structure).

Develop a function to retrieve the complete structure of the template associated with a list of SKUs, including milestones, tasks, and required documents. Return the response in JSON. - Add a function to return templates and tasks for programs.

*Definition of Ready:*
Will there be milestones assigned to the program? If so, which ones? However, what if a Document Gatering is completed for Telecom but not for Safety? The project begins? Or does the program begin when all documents are completed for all projects?


{noformat}Params:
["SKU-001", "SKU-002"]
Response:
{
  "milestones": [
    {
        "milestone_1": {
        "tasks": ["task_1", "task_2", ....]
      }
    }
  ],
  "documents_required": ["User Manual", "IMEI List", "....."]
}{noformat}

