column113:
08/Aug/25 2:57 PM;712020:bb4e8c28-91a0-4cd6-86e4-f66a70adb16f;h3. Report of Identified Observations

* If an error occurs in the *OIS*, the Opportunity *stage* should not be updated to *Closed Won* or *Prospecting*.

{color:#0747a6}→ On this point, a meeting was held with {color}[~accountid:5f2ddfb0c1b9f4001cdc43c3] {color:#0747a6} and the best solution has already been defined for cases where the stage is Closed Won.{color}


* When the quote is in *Ready for Review* status, the Opportunity status should not be allowed to be changed to *Closed Won*.

{color:#0747a6}→ Regarding this point, a meeting was held with {color}[~accountid:5f2ddfb0c1b9f4001cdc43c3] {color:#0747a6} and it was agreed to perform a check to validate whether there is a date in the “Sent to Client” field.{color}

* If a quote that is in *Closed Won* status is changed back to *Prospecting*, the status to which the Opportunity should return in the *OIS* must be defined.

{color:#0747a6}→ In this case, it is necessary to update the State Diagram {color}[~accountid:712020:1221cfec-034b-400d-9d4f-3d10e690f80a] [~accountid:712020:ff8381e9-46d4-4b6a-8559-724c87a90dba] {color:#0747a6}to clearly determine which state the OIS should return to when it moves back to Prospecting.{color}

column110:
08/Aug/25 12:27 PM;627bd786694943006f3538bf;{noformat}List<Account> accounts = [
    SELECT Id, Currency_Type__c
    FROM Account
    WHERE Currency_Type__c = ''
];


for(Account  acc: accounts){
    acc.Currency_Type__c = '$ USD';
}

UPDATE accounts;


{noformat}

